# ‚úÖ **STEP 1 ‚Äî Create IAM Policy for Images Bucket**

### 1Ô∏è‚É£ Go to AWS Console ‚Üí IAM

### 2Ô∏è‚É£ Left side ‚Üí Policies

### 3Ô∏è‚É£ Click **Create policy**

### 4Ô∏è‚É£ Select **JSON** tab

### 5Ô∏è‚É£ Paste this:

```
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "s3:PutObject",
        "s3:GetObject",
        "s3:DeleteObject"
      ],
      "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::projectname-prod-images/*"
    }
  ]
}
```

### 6Ô∏è‚É£ Click **Next** ‚Üí Next ‚Üí

### 7Ô∏è‚É£ Give name: **project-s3-images-policy**

### 8Ô∏è‚É£ Click **Create policy**

---

# ‚úÖ **STEP 2 ‚Äî Create IAM Policy for Payslips Bucket**

### 1Ô∏è‚É£ IAM ‚Üí Policies ‚Üí Create policy

### 2Ô∏è‚É£ Select **JSON**

### 3Ô∏è‚É£ Paste this:

```
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": [
        "s3:PutObject",
        "s3:GetObject"
      ],
      "Resource": "arn:aws:s3:::projectname-prod-payslips/*"
    }
  ]
}
```

‚ö†Ô∏è No Delete permission.

### 4Ô∏è‚É£ Next ‚Üí Next

### 5Ô∏è‚É£ Name: **project-s3-payslips-policy**

### 6Ô∏è‚É£ Create policy

---

# ‚úÖ **STEP 3 ‚Äî Create IAM Role for EC2**

### 1Ô∏è‚É£ Go to IAM ‚Üí Roles

### 2Ô∏è‚É£ Click **Create role**

### 3Ô∏è‚É£ Select **Trusted entity: AWS service**

### 4Ô∏è‚É£ Select **Use case: EC2**

### 5Ô∏è‚É£ Click **Next**

### 6Ô∏è‚É£ Attach policies:

* project-s3-images-policy
* project-s3-payslips-policy

üëá (Search them and tick both)

### 7Ô∏è‚É£ Click **Next**

### 8Ô∏è‚É£ Role name: **project-ec2-s3-role**

### 9Ô∏è‚É£ Create role

---

# ‚úÖ **STEP 4 ‚Äî Attach IAM Role to EC2 Instance**

### 1Ô∏è‚É£ Go to EC2 Dashboard

### 2Ô∏è‚É£ Click **Instances**

### 3Ô∏è‚É£ Select your backend EC2 instance

### 4Ô∏è‚É£ Click **Actions**

### 5Ô∏è‚É£ Select:

**Security ‚Üí Modify IAM Role**

### 6Ô∏è‚É£ Choose:

**project-ec2-s3-role**

### 7Ô∏è‚É£ Click **Update IAM role**

üéâ Now your EC2 has permissions to access both S3 buckets securely.

